<a href='http://www.ukclimbing.com/articles/page.php?id=9173' title='Read full article'><img src='https://cdn.ukclimbing.com/t/289455.jpg' width='150' height='105' alt='thumb' border='1' align='left' hspace='8' /></a><b>We recently came across some workshops organised by the University of Edinburgh as part of their Festival of Creative Learning at the University's Sport & Exercise Pleasance Sports Complex, named 'Sensory Learning in the Climbing Wall'. The sessions were well received by participants and focused on using the climbing wall as a tool for exploring different learning and teaching methods.</b><p>I got in touch with the climbing wall team leader, Gerry Crabbe, to find out more...</p>